cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper is about constructing and releasing a large-scale image steganalysis dataset, which involves image processing, computer vision, and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely since the dataset involves multimedia data. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible sub-category since steganography and steganalysis are related to cryptography and security. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are less likely but still possible since the paper mentions the use of machine learning algorithms and the dataset can be used for evaluating the performance of steganalysis algorithms.
